<P><H1 align=center>REGULAR OUTGOINGS – DC155</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>This screen shows a list of typical outgoings (eg. housekeeping, utilities, 
car and travel), about which details should be entered.</P>
<P><H3>Edit: </H3>to enter details about outgoings, highlight 
one of the outgoings and click Edit
<P></P>
<P><H3>Dialogue Box: </H3>this brings up the Regular Outgoings 
Details dialogue box. The field at the top shows which of the outgoings the box 
relates to. Enter the amount paid and the frequency, and click ‘Next’.
<P></P>
<P>The next outgoing on the list appears in the field at the top, and the 
process should be completed for each of the outgoings on the list. When the last 
on the list has been completed (‘Other’), click on ‘OK’ to return to DC155.</P>
<P>The details entered in the dialogue box now appear in the box at the top of 
the screen.</P>
<P><H3>Total Regular Outgoings: </H3>the Total Regular 
Outgoings field at the bottom right of the screen shows the calculated total
<P></P>
<P><H3>Edit: </H3>to amend any of the details, highlight the 
record to be changed and click on Edit
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>once all the information has been entered, 
click on ‘OK’, which leads to the next screen.
<P></P>
